<br>
1) Time Sinks - VT key anyone?  Shawl 8?  Seru Bane weapons?  Wood Elf Illusion crown?  Anyone?  Anyone?<br>
<br>
2) Camps - oh wait there are no camps.... that drop you need is a rare drop off a rare spawn... maybe you'll just get lucky and he'll be up when you drive by....<br>
<br>
3) Risk vs. Reward - this is a very poor example but it illustrates exactly what *I* mean - the new erudite guy in Paineel gives out an LoY quest... I figured out the quest (without spoilers, cong me~) and spent 8 hours gathering the shit for him (one unrezzed death too)... to get a range item I wouldn't put on my level 30 twink... so I gave him the item back, killed him, and I continue to kill him everytime I pass through Paineel.<br>
<br>
4) Class balancing - when a single character of a particular class can gain exp solo at a rate 10-15 times faster than I can with or without a group (and not because I suck, but rather because of a fault in the play balancing), then there is a problem.  I'm not saying that the solo classes need to be nerfed - but something should be done about the disparity<br>
<br>
5) Feeding of ghey expansions - I perceive that with the release of LoY, SOE has seen the light when it comes to expansions.  LoY was an &quot;expansion&quot; of nearly useless features and zones (charms?  wtf is a charm?) yet they were able to get most of us to pay the money for it.  Consider that SWG will be the entire UNIVERSE - how many useless expansions can you foresee there?  EQ2 will be released with just a subset of the currently playable zones... and they'll slowly drizzle out twice as many expansions to get us to the content level of the current EQ world... just watch.  Sorry - but I'm not paying $200+ for software AND $13 per month just to get somewhere close to the content I already have.<br>
<br>
6) Zone design issues - Pathing.  Pathing.  Pathing.  SOE, if you don't want it exploited... if you don't want people to cheat at your game... then fix it.  Otherwise stfu.  No... on second thought, fix it anyway because it's fucking annoying.<br>
<br>
7) Customer Service - yes I do list this, because it IS an issue.  However, as you can see, it's way down at the bottom.  Frankly, I don't expect a GM to rez me for my own stupidity.  I don't expect a GM to pop up immediately because some 13 year old is spouting bullshit in /ooc.  I don't expect a GM to give me back the 32plat that I looted while camping a charm in LoY when I LDed and got rolled back 3 minutes.  I DO expect a game that doesn't break all the damn time though.  I expect a game where the zones don't drop off and on (hello bazaar).  I do expect a game where a 6 hour patch is a 6 hour patch... not a 12 hour one.  I do expect a game where the issues being complained about are addressed first... the 47 people in San Diego with Linksys routers will need to wait till after they fix the pathing bugs for the 200,000 of that ARE able to play, k thx~<br>
<br>
Anyway, THIS is why I personally will not be playing SWG or EQ2. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121122" target="top">Ugzug</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arshesnei1>arshesnei1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(6/2/03 10:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9876.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I always find it funny when people bash this game, especially people that log on daily for hours. Yes this game has its flaws and yes those flaws can be tiresome but honestly this is a great game that has brought you great entertainment and if you no longer enjoy this game I suggest you stop playing it then.<br>
